                       </i>
                       <div>
                        <p>
                         <strong>
                          Departments and functions within the Chief Compliance organization support UCR's efforts to create an inclusive, accessible campus free from discrimination and harassment:
                         </strong>
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                         <li>
                          <a href="https://titleix.ucr.edu/">
                           The Title IX Office
                          </a>
                          coordinates UCR's efforts to prevent and respond to sexual harassment, sexual assault, dating/domestic violence, stalking, invasion of privacy, and other behavior prohibited by the
                          <a href="https://policy.ucop.edu/doc/4000385/SVSH" title="SVSH Policy">
                           UC Sexual Violence and Sexual Harassment Policy
                          </a>
                          .
                         </li>
                         <li>
                          <a href="/adasection-504-compliance-and-disability-inclusion-and-access" target="_blank" title="ADA/Section 504 Compliance and Disability Inclusion and Access">
                           The ADA/Rehabilitation Act Coordinator
                          </a>
                          oversees UCR's programs and policies relating to accessibility, accommodation and non-discrimination for those with disabilities.
                         </li>
                         <li>
                          The Fact-Finding team conducts
                          <a href="/investigations" title="Investigations">
                           investigations
                          </a>
                          of discrimination and harassment complaints.
                         </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>
                         Other UCR offices partnering in this work include:
                        </p>
                        <ol>
                         <li>
                          The
                          <a href="https://hr.ucr.edu/eeaa.html" title="EE/AA">
                           Equal Employment &amp; Affirmative Action (EE/AA) department
                          </a>
                          , within Human Resources, promotes UCR's commitment to non-discrimination, equal opportunity and affirmative action in employment.
                         </li>
                         <li>
                          The
                          <a href="https://diversity.ucr.edu/diversity.html">
                           Associate Vice Chancellor for Diversity &amp; Inclusion
                          </a>
                          oversees the development of programs and activities that support a culture of mutual respect and engagement, and advises the Chancellor on matters relating to inclusion, equity and climate.
                         </li>
                        </ol>
